{
  "text": "Our work is similar in method and objective to a large body of empirical work that aims to predict the effects on prices of alterations in the pattern of competition-see, for example, [CITATION_1] and Froeb, Tschantz, and Crooke [2003] . That research uses the differentiated-products Bertrand model and calibrates a demand system to data from a variety of sources. Most of the research focuses on the effects of mergers.",
